thread.title: Pa. boys and girls: Rustin soccer wins second straight Ches-Mont title
thread.title_full: Pa. boys and girls: Rustin soccer wins second straight Ches-Mont title

title: Pa. boys and girls: Rustin soccer wins second straight Ches-Mont title
text:
More coverage: Southeastern Pa. high school sports 
Suburban One National. Julia Guarini scored twice for host Abington in a 3-0 win over Truman. 
Tri-County League. Shira Perloff scored twice as visiting Barrack Hebrew defeated Del-Val Friends, 6-0, to take the league title. 
Public. Arryana Coleman scored twice as Franklin Towne Charter clinched first place with a 3-1 victory at Central. 
Sienna Doherty scored with five minutes left in regulation to send host Northeast to a 1-0 win over Science Leadership Academy. Boys' Soccer Evan Vare scored three times as No. 2 Central Bucks East (18-0) completed an undefeated regular season with a 4-0 Suburban One Continental win at Souderton. 
Austin Prime made three saves for his 12th shutout of the year. 
Elsewhere in the Continenal, Kyle Shue scored two first-half goals to spark No. 10 North Penn to a 4-1 win at Hatboro-Horsham. 
Suburban One National. Max Mykhyluk scored in host Council Rock North's 1-0 win over Bensalem. 
Friends Schools. Ashkon Ashrafion scored in OT to send Shipley to a 3-2 win over visiting George School. 
Public. DeAndre Fancy scored four minutes into OT to give Fels a 3-2 win at Franklin Towne Charter. Field Hockey Mary Cleary scored in overtime to lift visiting Lansdale Catholic past St. Hubert, 1-0, in the Catholic League.
In other Catholic League action, Allison Martin scored three times to power Bonner-Prendergast to a 6-0 win at Little Flower. Maggie Baldini made 11 saves. 
Ches-Mont. Taylor Orsi scored twice as Downingtown West won at West Chester Rustin, 4-1. 
Nonleague. Sarah Brennan scored to give Springfield (Delco) a 1-0 win at Interboro. Volleyball Kaleigh Oates 20 kills and 15 digs to lead host Villa Maria to a 3-0 victory over Mount St. Joseph in the Catholic Academies final.
It is the third consecutive title for the Hurricanes. 
Lauren Miller added 10 digs and six aces, Erin Zimmerman had four blocks, Alaina Acchione had 39 assists, and Emily Wynne finished with five kills, three blocks and two aces. Boys' Cross-Country Holy Ghost Prep's Callahan Lennon finished 3.1 miles in 16 minutes, 45 seconds to claim first place at the Bicentennial League championships at Tyler State Park in Newtown. Holy Ghost also won the team title with 20 points. Girls' Cross-Country Lower Moreland's Kerry Kovacs crossed in 19:56 to win the Bicentennial League title on the 3.1-mile course at Tyler State Park.
Christopher Dock won the team title with 24 points.
